keyValuePair.Value: Will you win promotion today?
Will you win promotion today?
At the end of a long season, everything rests on the last game. A win and you're guaranteed promotion. Are you happy your fate's in your own hands?
At the end of a long season, everything rests on the last game. A win and you're guaranteed promotion. Are you happy your fate's in your own hands?
I'm convinced we'll go up.
I'm proud of the boys. They've worked so hard to get us here and they've been so reliable on the big occasions. I'm counting on them being strong again today. We'll be up!
I'm proud of the boys. They've worked so hard to get us here and they've been so reliable on the big occasions. I'm counting on them being strong again today. We'll be up!
One last test.
This is like a cup final but it's great knowing it's what we do today that matters. The boys are determined. And we don't have to rely on anybody else but ourselves.
It's another challenge.
We've come a long way this season and we have to be happy going into the last game with promotion in our own hands. If the boys can perform like they have been, we'll be going up today.
Will you celebrate promotion today?
Your team's in a very strong position. A point today will be enough to clinch promotion. Are the boys ready? Do you expect them to get the job done?
The team's definitely good enough.
If I look at the group of players in our dressing room, I have to say that we're definitely good enough to go up. Now, it's up to the lads to go out and prove it just one more time.
We'll do what we always do.
We know we only need a point, but that hasn't affected our preparations. This team only knows how to play one way. I can promise our fans: we'll be going out there to win.
Let's not get carried away.
Yes, we're in a good position. Yes, I think we're a good team. But we know we're up against a dangerous %1s side. We all have to concentrate on our jobs.
The result you needed! How does it feel to win promotion?
There was incredible pressure on your players going into todays' game. But they came good, last game of the season, and got the result that's won you promotion. Relieved?
I'm relieved but I'm proud, too.
I think today is reward for how the players have performed all season. We've been consistently good from first game to last. The team has done this club proud, I believe.
I think today is reward for how the players have performed all season. We've been consistently good from first game to last. The team has done this club proud, I believe.
It's what we set out to do.
Promotion was the target at the start of the season. We knew what we were capable of. Now, though, we'll have to improve 100% if we're going to compete in the division above.
I'm just focused on next season now.

Look, well done to the players. But the important thing is the club is back where it belongs now. I'm just thinking now about being ready to face next season and the better teams we're going to be up against.
How frustrating a day was that?
You knew before the game that a draw would have been enough to see you clinch promotion. But it wasn't to be. What went wrong?
We'll have to come back from this.
It was a big, big chance and we failed to take it. I hope that teaches us all a lesson. We have to make sure we come back a better team in time for next season.
It was a big, big chance and we failed to take it. I hope that teaches us all a lesson. We have to make sure we come back a better team in time for next season.
We need to change things round.
Looking at the players in that dressing room, I have to wonder why they've missed out on the prize. Mentality! We need fresh faces in there to make sure this never happens again.
This isn't the only time we've missed our chance.

Today was all about drama and now disappointment. But, if we're honest, we know this isn't the only result that's cost us promotion. We've failed to collect some vital points in games all season long.
You knew what you had to do. What went wrong?
Your team went into today's game knowing a win would seal promotion. But you couldn't get the result you needed. How big a blow is this to the club?
We have to come back even stronger.
It's a shattering blow to all of us. But now it's about how we respond. Have we got the strength and resilience in our dressing room to make sure we go one better next season?
The players came up short, that's for sure.
That wasn't what I expected. But I've learnt something about this team today. Some of these players just haven't got the mentality that we need if we're going to take this club forwards.
It wasn't today that cost us promotion
There was so much pressure on today's game. Pressure that we put on ourselves with inconsistent performances earlier in the season. Those were the games that really cost us.
How good does promotion feel now?
How good does promotion feel now?
All the pressure was on this last game of the season, but the boys came through with flying colours. The win takes you up. You must be proud seeing this team promoted?
All the pressure was on this last game of the season, but the boys came through with flying colours. The win takes you up. You must be proud seeing this team promoted?
It was all down to hard work.
The boys have given absolutely everything every single game this season. Their work-rate and their togetherness made the difference today, too. The lads have deserved this success.
The boys have given absolutely everything every single game this season. Their work-rate and their togetherness made the difference today, too. The lads have deserved this success.
We've developed as a team, I think.
I think this team has grown over the course of the season. Today's achievement means the club are back where we belong. Now we'll have to be even better next time round.
Time to plan, now.
It's a great day for the club and for the fans. The players deserve to be celebrating. But promotion means we'll have to be even better next season. I'm already focused on that.
